caption: Food is great. Would like to be able to call the restaurant and order directly instead of paying/supporting Uber, Grub Hub, Cavier, Postmates..., but they don't take orders over the phone.
Charged more than said on menu. $20+ for a takeout noodles order, and the portion isn’t big.
Went here again over the weekend,  I just can't get enough of the rainbow salad!  We just love this place, great food and excellent service!

This place has awesome food at very reasonable prices! The staff is very friendly and they have complimentary tea while you wait. There is almost always a line if you don't get there within an hour of opening so get there early or be prepared to wait. The platha and dip appetizer is one of my favorite dishes ever, a must try!
Tea Leaf Salad...superty duperty yummy!!!!!  This is a great place, but get there early if you don't want to wait in line.

This is one of my all time favorite restuarants!  And that says a lot having been a SF resident for 20+ years.  I have regular cravings for the chicken dahl with coconut rice, and the tea salad.  I suggest going for lunch on a weekday to …

A little pricey for what we got.  The service was good and everything, I just wasn't blown away by the food.  Maybe it's just different from what I'm used to since I had never had any Bermese food before.
Food is very flavorful and the service is very prompt.  There is a good reason why this place is crowded.  Burmese food in general is delicious, but this is the best in SF.

I love this restaurant in San Carlos.  The food is consistently outstanding.  The samosas have a delicate crust and the inner contents so smooth and savory.  The tea leaf salad can’t be beat, and the garlic noodles...awesome!  Can’t wait to return!
Very mediocre. No atmosphere.
The service was great and super friendly, offering free vegetable soup. The entree I got, broccoli beef, tasted only average though. The portion is huge.
Great food!
burmese food, very delicious. service is consistently above par. the bill was good for what you get. food is like a restaurant in louisville i loved.
This reminds me of my friend's family cooking growing up. So delicious. Had the beef curry and the sticky rice for dessert. Absolutely fantastic. Couldn't ask for more.
Friendly staff and good food
Food was excellent and lovely service.  My only "con" observation is there was no atmosphere and quite bland decor. Otherwise food was good, fairly priced and nice presentation.
Great food

Chile Basil Lamb was delicious, as was the Burmese Basmati Rice. The Burmese Pad Thai was good but nothing special. A great place to dine before the symphony or opera. The prices were on the high end.

Great food
Great service. Bad food.
OMG I loved the place, relatively new I guess, but their food is really good, anything u order is delicious and tasty, good service, and they kept some of the original decorations of the place.
Service & food are great. The ambience in the dining area is not really cozy but clean.

When I walked by the place, it looks like a warehouse with big kitchen equipment, no dining area. So I was skeptical about it. But I got totally surprise of the taste and the service I got. Hope I will come back soon
Good food at a reasonable price served in a spacious, minimalist setting close to SF Civic Center.

The mango chicken lacked mango flavor and cost $10 with rice. While I did not have the best first impression of this restaurant it is close to city hall and is an option for people who can afford it. I hope they have  garlic & ginger …

Burmese Fast food/express on Van Ness! Food was delicious.... I would definitely go back!!

Lunch buffet vs sit down dinner is pretty different. I don't have issue with the food, but was sad to see the buffet quick pick was only for lunch. Waited longers than wanted for take out, had I realized the different set up and would have made more time for myself. BUT those samosas are DELICIOUS and I liked the food over all!
Ordered delivery which arrived in a timely manner, hot  & correct.  DEELISHUS! Flavorful & Spicy. Had the spicy dumplings which coupled with the cooling cucumber salad. Definitely ordering again.
GREAT  FOOD AND DRINKS

Delicious food! I'd never had Burmese food before; loved it. I'll be back.
Pricey but good food with a trendy vibe, full bar, and a wine list on an iPad. Gluten-free menu available. Waitstaff is knowledgeable about gluten and cross-contamination risks.
Great Asian food. The service was a bit slow, but the food was good and the atmosphere was nice.
Fresh and delicious!
Tea leaf salad was really good. My husband liked his curry dish too. A little pricey for the amount of food you get though.
Great food, fresh and crunchy salads, amazing chicken, best fermented tea leaves salad ever!!!

Good burmese menu
Ordered take out... The Nan Gyi Dok was awesome. Thick rice noodles, rich creamy curry, red onions and more. I'd come back for that dish again.
Having it here yet but seems like a place to go to it's always busy so one day I will try it I love Burmese food.
Very traditional food
Get the barata chicken appetizer. The portions are very generous and they have a surprisingly good wine selection!

A hidden gem on Polk Street. There is never a wait because it's significantly more upscale than its neighborhood. The rainbow salad and samosa soup are on par with the best of the city. Service is attentive, and we haven't ordered a bad dish from the menu yet. Def recommend the coconut rice with whatever else you get.

Great food, warm welcome. Last night was a nice surprise, the samosa was perfect, the tealeaf salad was a good size to share and very tasty, especially with the cabbage. Garlic noodles and fried banana with mango ice cream for dessert. And last but not least, the waitress was very attentive and pleasant. A great evening.
Excellent, fresh Burmese cuisine--gives Burma Superstar and Mandelay a run for their money!

Food was okay. Not as hyped as many people say. Pricey small portions. And tip is included in price. Twenty percent. But it is expect to go to a place like this. Looks nice it is good service. I hear the Palo Alto on is better.
When I first walked they did not even greet me, and were not even that busy. The food was not that great, and they tried to oversell me with food and drinks.

Fabulous Burmese food. The tea leaf salad alone is worth coming to try. Everything was delicious. Other favorites were the Garlic Noodles and the eggplant. Great wine list. The dining room is elegant without being pretentious. Showed up on Sunday and had no issues seating a party of six. I wish parking was like that.
